reviews.text:
Well it is a railway station but there isn't much else to be thankful for.

the trains in one direction head towards Manchester and in the other they head towards Warrington.

This station has no car parking available at all and there are no closed-circuit television cameras here.

There is a small covered waiting area on both sides of the tracks, and there is also a payment machine on one of the platforms.

There is no digital display anywhere, so the only way you have any idea that a train might be heading towards the railway station is down to a loudspeaker located on the platforms.

I can't say anything else really because there isn't anything else to say.
Friendly station cat greets me every morning.
